Description: Papyrus (three fragments that appear to join). Cartonnage. Demotic account on both recto and verso. Ends of 20+x lines of one column and beginnings of 32 lines of a second column on the recto. The top and bottom margins are preserved. On the verso traces of numbers.
Curator's comments: Of the first column on the recto there are just a series of numbers preserved. The second column just preserves the very beinnings of all the lines.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (380997) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/380997)
